---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const includes = [
  "Home page", "Service pages", "About page", "Contact page",
  "Mobile first design", "Google Maps integration", "Fast page speed",
  "Local SEO structure", "HTTPS security", "Analytics",
  "Online booking", "Tap to call buttons", "Custom coding",
  "Google Business Profile integration",
];

const trades = [
  "Hair salons", "Barbershops", "Color specialists", "Balayage and highlights",
  "Blowout bars", "Extensions", "Bridal and event styling", "Men's grooming",
  "Booth renters", "Suite owners",
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do you build websites for salons in other states?",
    a: "Yes. I'm based in Big Bear, California, but I build websites for salons and barbershops all over the United States. Because everything is done by phone, email, and video call, we never need to meet in person and your location is never a problem. When we get on our first call, I learn your services, the towns and neighborhoods you serve, and the kind of clients you want more of. Then I build your website around those local searches, so the people in your area looking for a stylist have a better chance of finding your chair. Every website is built around your local market, your services, and the clients you're trying to reach, not around my location. So whether you're one town over or across the country, you get the same custom coded website, the same honest pricing, and the same person answering when you need something changed.",
  },
  {
    q: "What kinds of salons do you work with?",
    a: "I build websites for hair salons and grooming businesses of almost every kind: full service salons, barbershops, color specialists, balayage and highlight studios, blowout bars, extension artists, bridal and event stylists, men's grooming shops, booth renters, and suite owners. The common thread is simple: if your clients find you by searching online and then book or call, a website built the right way will bring you more of them. Your services shape how I build the site. A color specialist needs a gallery of before and after transformations; a barbershop needs a fast tap to call button and walk in hours up front; a bridal stylist needs a booking page that captures the date and the look. I build each site around the services you actually offer and the appointments you actually want, not a generic template with your logo dropped on top. If you're not sure whether your salon fits, it almost certainly does. Book a free call, tell me what you do behind the chair, and I'll tell you straight how a website would help you get found and get booked.",
  },
  {
    q: "Can clients book appointments online from my website?",
    a: "Yes, and for most salons it's the single biggest win. I can wire online booking right into your website so a new client can find you on their phone, see your services, and book a time without ever picking up the phone. That matters because a lot of people look for a stylist after hours, when you're at home and the shop is closed, and a booking button captures that appointment instead of losing it to the next salon on the list. If you already use a system like Square, Vagaro, Booksy, GlossGenius, or Calendly, I connect your website to it so everything still lands in the calendar you already trust. If you don't have one yet, I'll help you pick one that fits how you run your chair. Either way, the goal is the same: make it as easy to book you at midnight as it is at noon.",
  },
  {
    q: "Will my website show a gallery of my work?",
    a: "Yes, and your work is the best selling tool you have. A clean gallery of your cuts, colors, and finished styles tells a new client more than any paragraph of text ever could, because people choosing a stylist want to see real results before they sit in your chair. I build a photo gallery into your website and set it up so it stays fast and sharp on a phone, where almost everyone will see it. Before and after shots of a color correction or a fresh transformation are especially powerful, so I'll show you the few simple shots worth grabbing on your phone after an appointment. If you don't have a full library of photos yet, that's fine, we launch with what you have and the gallery only gets stronger as you add to it. Your best work should be the first thing a new client sees.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do I own my website?",
    a: "When your website is finished, you own the code, your domain name, and your hosting account. Nothing is rented and you're never locked into a monthly website subscription. Most website builders work differently. You pay every month, but the website isn't truly yours. If you stop paying, the site often disappears. I build websites in clean code that you own outright. If you ever decide to work with someone else, you can. Your website belongs to your business, not to me.",
  },
  {
    q: "How much does a website cost?",
    a: "It depends on your salon, so I won't throw out a number that turns out wrong. Here's the honest range you'll see in the market: on the cheap end, builders like Wix run around $30 a month forever, and you never own the site. On the high end, large agencies charge $10,000 or more, often with an ongoing monthly retainer attached. I build custom websites that you own outright and price them in between, with one clear number scoped to your business. What moves that number is straightforward: how many services you offer, whether you serve more than one location, and whether you want extras like online booking, a full photo gallery, missed call text back, or client reminders. Before I quote anything, I learn your services and your service area on a free call, so the price reflects your actual salon instead of a guess. You'll get a fixed proposal with exactly what's included and no surprises later. If you want the full breakdown of what goes into website pricing, I wrote a plain English guide on it, and then we can get on a call so I can give you your real number.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I already have a website?",
    a: "That's common, and you have two good options. The first is a full rebuild on the same domain. This is usually the better path if your current site is on Wix, Squarespace, GoDaddy, or another builder, because those sites are rented, hard to rank, and you never truly own them. I rebuild it in clean code that you own outright, keeping your domain and anything worth saving, like your booking link and your photos. The second option is a straight review. If you already have a decent site, I'll look at it and tell you honestly what's working, what's hurting you, and whether a rebuild is even worth your money. Sometimes the answer is that you only need a few fixes, and I'll say so rather than sell you something you don't need. Either way, the call is free and you walk away knowing where you stand. The one thing I'd caution against is leaving a slow or outdated website up while you decide, because for a busy salon, an old site can cost you new clients every week it stays online.",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Websites for Hair Salons That Fill Your Chairs"
  description="Custom websites for hair salons and barbershops, built for Google Search with online booking and a gallery of your work to turn searches into booked appointments. You own everything; no monthly rental. Built in the USA."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "Website Design for Hair Salons",
      "serviceType": "Website design for hair salons and barbershops",
      "provider": { "@id": "https://reynahouse.ai/#org" },
      "areaServed": ["United States"],
      "description": "Custom coded websites for hair salons and barbershops, built for Google Search with online booking and a gallery of work to convert searches into booked appointments. The owner keeps the code, domain, and hosting outright.",
      "url": "https://reynahouse.ai/websites-for-hair-salons/",
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": faqs.map((f) => ({
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": f.q,
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a },
      })),
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Local Service Businesses", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/websites-for-local-service-businesses/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Websites for Hair Salons", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/websites-for-hair-salons/" },
      ],
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <Header />

  <main class="page">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <article class="intro">
      <div class="intro__container">
        <nav class="crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> <a href="/websites-for-local-service-businesses/">Local Service Businesses</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> Websites for Hair Salons
        </nav>
        <span class="overline">BUILT FOR THE CHAIR</span>
        <h1 class="h1">Websites for Hair Salons That Fill Your Chairs</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          You do beautiful work, but online the salon with the better website
          usually gets the booking. If new clients can't find you on Google,
          or they land on an outdated website with no way to book, they often
          choose someone else before they ever sit in your chair.
        </p>
        <p class="body body--gold">
          Your website has one job: help new clients find your salon
          online and make it easy to book, call, or see your work. That's what
          every website I build is designed to do.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- LIVE EXAMPLE -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">See a Live Salon Site I Built</h2>
        <p class="body">
          This is a real salon website I built and put online: a gallery of the
          work, easy online booking, fast tap to call, and a layout made to turn
          a search into a booked chair. It's the same kind of site I'd build for
          you.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top: 8px;">
          <a href="https://villagehairsmith.com/" class="btn btn--primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View villagehairsmith.com &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT YOU GET -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">What You Get</h2>
        <div class="cards">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Built for Google Search</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Every website is built around the searches your clients actually make; your services, your styles, your city, and the appointments you want more of.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Built to Get the Booking</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Online booking, tap to call buttons, clear calls to action, and fast loading pages that make it easy for a new client to book you on the spot.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">A Gallery of Your Work</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Cuts, colors, and before and after transformations shown in a clean gallery, because nothing sells a stylist like real results.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Mobile First Design</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Most clients find a salon from their phone. Every website is designed for mobile first.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">You Own Everything</h3>
            <p class="card__body">You own the code, domain, hosting, and content. No subscriptions. No website rental.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Optional Growth Tools</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Add appointment reminders, missed call text back, lead tracking, AI chat, and automations whenever you're ready.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- INCLUDES -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Every Website I Build Includes</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          {includes.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BUILT FOR LOCAL SEARCH -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Built for Local Search</h2>
        <p class="body">
          Most salons don't need clients across the country;
          they need clients nearby.
        </p>
        <p class="body">
          Every website is structured around your service area so people searching
          for a stylist in your city have a better chance of finding your salon.
          Whether you serve one neighborhood or several towns, your website is built
          around the locations that matter most.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- COST -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">What a Website Costs</h2>
        <p class="body">Every salon is different.</p>
        <p class="body">
          Some websites cost $30 per month forever because you never own them.
          Others cost $10,000 or more through large agencies with ongoing retainers.
        </p>
        <p class="body">
          I build custom websites that you own outright. Before I give
          you a price, I learn about your services, your service area, and what your
          salon actually needs, so you receive one honest number with no
          surprises.
          <a class="inline-link" href="/small-business-website-cost/">See the full breakdown of what a website costs.</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHY DIFFERENT -->
    <section class="section section--dark">
      <div class="section__container">
        <span class="overline overline--light">WHY MINE IS DIFFERENT</span>
        <h2 class="h2 h2--light">Built in the USA, and You Own It</h2>
        <p class="body body--light">
          Many low cost website companies reduce prices by outsourcing development
          overseas or locking businesses into monthly website rentals.
        </p>
        <p class="body body--light">
          I build every website myself in the United States using clean code. When
          the project is finished, you own it. If you ever need help, I'm still
          here because I've earned your business, not because you're trapped.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHO I BUILD FOR -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Who I Build Websites For</h2>
        <div class="trades">
          {trades.map((t) => <span class="trade">{t}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p class="body trades__note">
          If your salon depends on local clients finding you online, I can
          build a website designed around that goal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">How It Works</h2>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Book a Free Call</h3>
            <p>Tell me about your services, service area, and goals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Receive a Fixed Proposal</h3>
            <p>You'll receive one clear price with exactly what's included.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Launch Your Website</h3>
            <p>Most websites are completed in about a week. After your review, your site launches under your ownership.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section section--cta">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Ready to Fill More Chairs?</h2>
        <p class="body">
          Tell me your services and your service area, and I'll show you what a website
          built for Google Search and online booking can do for your salon. Book a free
          call; no pressure, no obligation.
        </p>
        <div class="cta__actions">
          <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn--primary">Book a Free Call &rarr;</a>
          <a href="tel:+19093410243" class="btn btn--ghost">Or call 909-341-0243</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container section__container--narrow">
        <h2 class="h2">Common Questions From Salon Owners</h2>
        {faqs.map((f) => (
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq__q">{f.q}</summary>
            <p class="faq__a">{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RELATED -->
    <section class="related">
      <div class="related__container">
        <p class="related__title">Keep Reading</p>
        <div class="related__grid">
          <a class="related__card" href="/websites-for-local-service-businesses/">
            <span>Websites for Local Service Businesses</span>
            <small>See every trade and service I build for.</small>
          </a>
          <a class="related__card" href="/small-business-website-cost/">
            <span>What Does a Small Business Website Cost?</span>
            <small>The four ways to buy one, and the rent versus own trap.</small>
          </a>
          <a class="related__card" href="/missed-call-text-back/">
            <span>Missed Call Text Back</span>
            <small>Stop losing bookings to voicemail when you can't pick up.</small>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page { background-color: var(--white); }
  .intro { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, #1a1a2e 100%); padding: 72px 24px 64px; }
  .intro__container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .crumbs { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--tan); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .crumbs a { color: var(--copper-light); }
  .crumbs a:hover { color: var(--copper); }
  .overline { display: block; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .h1 { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--white); font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 3.6rem); line-height: 1.05; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .lede { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--white); font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section--tint { background-color: var(--cream); }
  .section--dark { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--forest) 0%, #1a2a1c 100%); }
  .section--cta { background-color: var(--white); text-align: center; }
  .section__container { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section__container--narrow { max-width: 760px; }
  .h2 { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.6rem); line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .h2--light { color: var(--white); }
  .body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .body--light { color: var(--cream); }
  .body--gold { color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; }
  .inline-link { color: var(--copper-dark); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .inline-link:hover { color: var(--copper); }

  .cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px; }
  .card__title { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .card__body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .checklist { list-style: none; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 10px 28px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .checklist li { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 1rem; padding: 6px 0 6px 28px; position: relative; }
  .checklist li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--copper-dark); font-weight: 700; }

  .trades { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .trade { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--navy); background: var(--cream); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 999px; padding: 8px 16px; }
  .trades__note { margin-top: 28px; }

  .steps { display: grid; gap: 16px; margin-top: 28px; counter-reset: step; }
  .step { position: relative; padding: 20px 20px 20px 68px; background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; }
  .step::before { counter-increment: step; content: counter(step); position: absolute; left: 20px; top: 20px; width: 34px; height: 34px; display: grid; place-items: center; background: var(--copper); color: var(--white); font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; font-size: 1.25rem; border-radius: 50%; }
  .step h3 { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .step p { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .cta__actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; margin-top: 28px; }
  .btn { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; padding: 14px 26px; border-radius: 8px; transition: background-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease; }
  .btn--primary { background-color: var(--copper); color: var(--white); }
  .btn--primary:hover { background-color: #b8843f; }
  .btn--ghost { border: 1px solid var(--navy); color: var(--navy); }
  .btn--ghost:hover { background-color: var(--navy); color: var(--white); }
  .btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--copper); outline-offset: 2px; }

  .faq { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--tan); padding: 16px 0; }
  .faq__q { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-dark); font-size: 0.95rem; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; padding: 4px 0; }
  .faq__q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq__q::before { content: '+ '; font-weight: 700; }
  details[open] .faq__q::before { content: '− '; }
  .faq__a { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.97rem; line-height: 1.7; padding: 12px 0 4px; }

  .related { background: var(--cream); padding: 48px 24px; }
  .related__container { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .related__title { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-dark); font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .related__grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
  .related__card { display: block; background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; padding: 18px; transition: border-color 0.2s ease; }
  .related__card:hover { border-color: var(--copper); }
  .related__card span { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3; }
  .related__card small { display: block; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5; }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .checklist { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .related__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
